Hi, my name is Meryle and I am one of the people pov asked<br>
to facilitate this discussion.  De'Yona's situation has brought<br>
us to key and very heavy issues -- pregnancy, use of birth <br>
control, what kinds of choices do young women <br>
want to be able to make, how do life events affect us.   While <br>
we can't know what was in De'Yona's mind, it would be <br>
helpful to think about what kinds of choices girls would like to<br>
make.   <br><br>
I see people posting messages with very different <br>
opinions about these issues.  I hope that, together, we can <br>
keep this a place where we can respect each other's opinions.<br><br>
In that spirit, I'd like to ask some questions about choices:<br>
What kinds of choices are you and your friends making<br>
about pregnancy?  about birth control?  How hard is it to make<br>
those choices happen?  Are the people you are involved with<br>
helping you keep those choices?<br><br>
